&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Area Coordinator / Construction Coordinator supports field execution activities within a designated area of a semiconductor manufacturing facility project. This role is responsible for coordinating contractors, tracking progress, supporting construction planning, and ensuring alignment between engineering, construction, and commissioning teams. The position plays a critical role in maintaining schedule, safety, and quality during fast-paced, highly technical construction and startup phases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate daily construction activities within an assigned area, ensuring work is executed safely, efficiently, and in alignment with project schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a field liaison between contractors, subcontractors, engineering teams, and project management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track installation progress and provide regular updates on construction status, constraints, and risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support lookahead planning (2-week / 6-week schedules) and assist in identifying potential schedule impacts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor contractor performance, manpower levels, and work sequencing within the assigned area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and escalate field issues, including design conflicts, material shortages, and installation challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with resolution of RFIs (Requests for Information) and coordinate with engineering teams to clarify design intent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in daily/weekly coordination meetings, safety briefings, and progress reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure work is performed in compliance with project specifications, drawings, and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support system turnover and commissioning activities by coordinating punch list completion and readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate field documentation, including daily reports, issue logs, and progress tracking tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote and enforce Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) standards across all site activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
