&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Certified Welding Inspector working with the LotusWorks team, you will join our client site in the semiconductor sector. This role is based at a leading semiconductor manufacturing facility in Chandler, Arizona and will support construction quality activities across mechanical, process mechanical, and structural systems during facility expansion and construction projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform welding inspections in accordance with applicable codes, standards, project specifications, and quality requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct visual inspections of welds on stainless steel, carbon steel, and plastic piping systems, as well as structural components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and interpret Welding Procedure Specifications (WPS), Procedure Qualification Records (PQR), and related quality documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify the qualification of welders and welding operators.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor welding activities to ensure compliance with approved procedures, project requirements, and safety protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, document, and track welding deficiencies and verify corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and maintain accurate inspection records, reports, and turnover documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with construction, quality, engineering, and client teams to resolve welding-related issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all relevant safety, quality, and project standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project turnover activities through completion of required inspection and quality documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in continuous improvement initiatives to enhance quality processes and project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in welding inspection, preferably within semiconductor construction, industrial construction, mission-critical facilities, advanced manufacturing, or similar environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience inspecting welds on stainless steel, carbon steel, and plastic piping systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of mechanical, process mechanical, and structural construction practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of welding processes, materials, and quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in interpreting technical drawings, specifications, isometric drawings, and welding documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with construction quality control and inspection processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail and strong analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and teamwork abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to maintaining a safe and quality-focused work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Education / Licenses / Certifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess a current Certified Welding Inspector (CWI) certification through the American Welding Society (AWS) or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional certifications related to welding inspection or

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Chemical and Gas (PSSS) Commissioning Engineer is responsible for supporting the commissioning and turnover of Process Support Systems (PSSS) within a semiconductor manufacturing facility. This role partners closely with construction teams, equipment vendors, contractors, and client stakeholders to ensure chemical and gas systems are safely transitioned from construction to operations. The ideal candidate is highly organized, collaborative, and able to effectively coordinate activities across multiple disciplines in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1jq9t4p&quot; data-start=&quot;537&quot; data-end=&quot;667&quot;&gt;Coordinate the handover, commissioning, and turnover of chemical and gas cabinets within a semiconductor manufacturing facility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;90vn1a&quot; data-start=&quot;668&quot; data-end=&quot;812&quot;&gt;Support commissioning activities for Process Support Systems (PSSS), ensuring systems are prepared for safe startup and operational readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;2knzbu&quot; data-start=&quot;813&quot; data-end=&quot;982&quot;&gt;Work closely with construction teams, contractors, equipment vendors, and client representatives to facilitate successful system turnover and commissioning activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;141jzly&quot; data-start=&quot;983&quot; data-end=&quot;1125&quot;&gt;Coordinate daily commissioning schedules, track progress against project milestones, and communicate status updates to project stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;ks8v85&quot; data-start=&quot;1126&quot; data-end=&quot;1271&quot;&gt;Verify system readiness by confirming completion of construction activities, documentation, inspections, and required pre-commissioning checks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1d9f9r&quot; data-start=&quot;1272&quot; data-end=&quot;1423&quot;&gt;Participate in field walkdowns to identify incomplete work, deficiencies, or punch list items that could impact commissioning or turnover activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;b9h4of&quot; data-start=&quot;1424&quot; data-end=&quot;1576&quot;&gt;Assist in coordinating equipment startup, functional testing, and system verification activities in accordance with approved commissioning procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;bb1znk&quot; data-start=&quot;1577&quot; data-end=&quot;1741&quot;&gt;Identify, communicate, and help resolve issues affecting commissioning schedules, system readiness, or project execution while escalating concerns as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;132m29c&quot; data-start=&quot;1742&quot; data-end=&quot;1904&quot;&gt;Maintain accurate commissioning documentation, turnover packages, testing records, and project tracking logs throughout all phases of the commissioning process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;fxfz0t&quot; data-start=&quot;1905&quot; data-end=&quot;2063&quot;&gt;Ensure commissioning activities are performed in accordance with site safety requirements, quality standards, project specifications, and client procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;6lo7hv&quot; data-start=&qu

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Commissioning Engineer (QCx Engineer) to support the commissioning, qualification, and startup of critical systems within a semiconductor manufacturing facility. This role is responsible for ensuring that mechanical, electrical, process utility, and building systems are installed, tested, and operating in accordance with project specifications, operational requirements, and applicable regulatory standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have experience in commissioning mission-critical or industrial facilities and possess a strong understanding of semiconductor facility infrastructure, including HVAC, cleanroom environments, process utilities, building automation systems, and electrical distribution systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the planning, execution, and documentation of commissioning activities for semiconductor facility projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct functional performance testing (FPT) and system verification activities for mechanical, electrical, and process utility systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify equipment and systems operate in accordance with design specifications, owner requirements, and applicable industry standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the development and execution of commissioning plans, test procedures, scripts, and turnover documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform project risk assessments prior to major testing and commissioning activities and implement appropriate control measures to ensure safe execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong safety-first mindset and actively promote a culture of safety throughout all project phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with project teams, contractors, vendors, and facility personnel to support system startup, troubleshooting, and issue resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review construction and installation quality to identify deficiencies and support corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support punch list management, system turnover, and project closeout activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain professional working relationships with clients, contractors, vendors, and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare detailed commissioning reports, test documentation, and technical summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all commissioning documentation is completed accurately and maintained in accordance with project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in factory acceptance testing (FAT), site acceptance testing (SAT), and integrated systems testing as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–5 years of commissioning, qualification, startup, facilities engineering, or mission-critical infrastructure experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting semiconductor, advanced manufacturing, pharmaceutical, life sciences, data center, or other highly regulated industrial facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of mechanical and/or electrical systems including:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HVAC systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Chilled water systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will lead field commissioning activities on large-scale semiconductor construction projects, supporting the successful startup, testing, and turnover of critical facility systems. You will work closely with project managers, design professionals, subcontractors, vendors, and client stakeholders to ensure systems are commissioned safely, efficiently, and in accordance with project requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the project management team in planning and coordinating commissioning and startup activities to maintain project schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a thorough understanding of system startup requirements, including predecessor and successor activities necessary for successful commissioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and manage the project QA/QC Program, coordinate QA/QC Specialists, and ensure subcontractors comply with approved QA/QC plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform onsite inspections, including underground utilities and owner-furnished equipment, to verify construction quality and readiness for startup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review construction documents, specifications, sequences of operation, technical manuals, submittals, and RFIs to support successful project execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate commissioning activities with project managers, design teams, subcontractors, vendors, and client stakeholders across multiple disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead startup meetings and coordinate construction sequencing to ensure systems are safe, complete, and ready for startup, testing, and turnover.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary client-facing point of contact for commissioning activities, communicating project status, risks, technical issues, and commissioning progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain commissioning plans, schedules, reporting systems, RACI matrices, issue logs, meeting minutes, and turnover documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate Operational Acceptance Testing (OAT), Functional Performance Testing (FPT), Integrated Systems Testing (IST), and system turnover while driving deficiencies and punch list items to resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Authorities Having Jurisdiction (AHJs), testing agencies, and third-party commissioning providers to ensure regulatory and project compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize owner training and support project closeout activities to ensure a successful system handover.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear verbal, written, and electronic communication with project stakeholders throughout all phases of the project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years of commissioning experience on semiconductor, mission-critical, or industrial construction projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of commissioning methodologies, startup, functional testing, integrated systems testing, and system turnover.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience coordinating commissioning activities across multiple disciplines, subcontractors, vendors, and project stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-start=&quot;750&quot; data-end=&quot;1078&quot;&gt;LotusWorks is seeking an experienced Commissioning Manager to lead commissioning activities on large-scale semiconductor or mission-critical projects. This role will serve as the General Contractor’s commissioning representative and act as a key interface between construction teams, the client, and commissioning personnel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1080&quot; data-end=&quot;1305&quot;&gt;The Commissioning Manager will oversee the planning, execution, and coordination of commissioning activities across complex mechanical and utility systems while maintaining schedule, quality, and factory readiness priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage commissioning personnel and processes across all project phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1383&quot; data-end=&quot;1463&quot;&gt;Act as the GC commissioning representative between construction teams and the clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1383&quot; data-end=&quot;1463&quot;&gt;Oversee commissioning of complex HVAC and utility systems, including&amp;nbsp;Oil Free Air, process cooling water, purified water, chemical and gas systems, cooling towers, and chilled water systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1383&quot; data-end=&quot;1463&quot;&gt;Implement and maintain commissioning quality control processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1383&quot; data-end=&quot;1463&quot;&gt;Manage and track construction and commissioning KPIs.&lt;/li&gt;
