&lt;li&gt;Conducts required Job Hazard Analysis (JHAs) to ensure a safe and compliance work environment for all construction personnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates subcontractor work methods, schedule and crews as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tracks and follows up on open it

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The CSA / Room Ready Commissioning Engineer supports commissioning activities associated with Civil, Structural, and Architectural (CSA) systems within a semiconductor manufacturing facility. This role collaborates with construction teams, project managers, commissioning personnel, contractors, and client representatives to ensure facility spaces are completed, inspected, and prepared for equipment installation and operational readiness. The ideal candidate is detail-oriented, eager to develop technical expertise, and motivated to contribute to the successful delivery of a highly complex manufacturing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform inspections and commissioning activities for Civil, Structural, and Architectural (CSA) systems within a semiconductor manufacturing facility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct room readiness assessments to verify that construction activities are complete and spaces are prepared for equipment installation and future operational requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review construction drawings, specifications, and project documentation to support inspection activities and verify compliance with project requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, document, and communicate construction deficiencies, quality issues, and incomplete work requiring resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with construction contractors, project teams, and client stakeholders to track progress and support timely closeout of outstanding items.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete detailed inspection reports, punch lists, and commissioning documentation to maintain accurate project records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support verification of room conditions, including cleanliness, accessibility, finishes, structural elements, and other CSA requirements necessary for equipment installation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with coordination of commissioning activities across multiple project disciplines and construction phases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor assigned areas and prioritize inspections to support project milestones and overall facility readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in project meetings and provide updates regarding inspection findings, documentation status, and readiness activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work safely and follow all client site procedures, quality standards, and commissioning requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Civil, Structural, and Architectural (CSA) construction concepts and principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interpret construction drawings, specifications, and technical documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail with the ability to identify quality issues and construction deficiencies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills with the ability to maintain accurate documentation and inspection records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective written and verbal communication skills with the ability to collaborate across multidisciplinary teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficie

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is seeking an experienced EHS Site Specialist to provide dedicated, embedded health and safety support to our growing Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance (O&amp;amp;M) teams at semiconductor manufacturing campuses across the United States. This is a hands-on, field-forward role designed to integrate directly into day-to-day O&amp;amp;M operations, ensuring LotusWorks personnel work safely, compliantly, and in alignment with both LotusWorks EHS standards and site requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The EHS Site Specialist will report directly to the LotusWorks O&amp;amp;M Manager and maintain a functional alignment with the LotusWorks EHS Manager. This dual reporting structure ensures operational agility while preserving program consistency, document control, and regulatory compliance across all sites.&lt;/p&gt;
