&lt;li&gt;Monitor site conditions including housekeeping, access control, PPE compliance, and safe work practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface directly with site EHS and facilities counterparts on site-specific safety requirements, permitting, and incidents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote Good Catch reporting and encourage other leading indicator methods across sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PPE &amp;amp; Equipment Inspections&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct regular inspection of personal protective equipment including full body harnesses, lanyards, SRLs, SCBA/PAPR, hearing protection, and task-specific PPE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain PPE inspection records and flag defective equipment for removal from service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect tools, aerial work platforms (MEWPs), ladders, and scaffolding components used by O&amp;amp;M teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support PPE needs assessments and coordinate with the EHS Coordinator on proc

