&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1wto8jy&quot; data-start=&quot;1530&quot; data-end=&quot;1574&quot;&gt;Review thermal infrared (IR) scan reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dat

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Electrical Commissioning Engineer plays a key role in the acceptance phase of projects, ensuring electrical systems are installed, tested, validated, and documented in line with approved procedures and project requirements. This position involves hands-on commissioning activities, troubleshooting, and supporting the successful completion of electrical systems for mission-critical facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute electrical commissioning activities including testing, validation, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform technical reviews of electrical designs and develop test scripts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct functional and performance tests on electrical equipment and systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with safety standards, isolation procedures, and LOTO protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate documentation and reporting for commissioning progress and results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with project teams to ensure alignment and timely completion of tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement initiatives and training programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to you in your role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of electrical systems, commissioning processes, and safety standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to interpret technical documentation and execute test procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and coordination abilities within multidisciplinary teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Education / Licenses / Certifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;QQI Level 6 Advanced Trade Certificate or Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering or related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proof of education, licenses, and certifications will be required where applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;LotusWorks is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any kind. We are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where all employees feel valued, respected, and empowered.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;LotusWorks is an Engineering Services provider specializing in managing Commissioning, Construction Services, Calibration, Operations &amp;amp; Maintenance scopes of work within global manufacturing facilities. LotusWorks operates globally across EMEA and North America partnering with the world&#39;s leading manufacturers across the Semiconductor, Pharmaceutical &amp;amp; Biologics, Medical Device and Data Centre sectors. Our team of Engineering and Technical professionals is immersed in cutting-edge technologies and innovations. LotusWorks is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace, integral to our people-first approach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Electrical Commissioning Lead, you will take ownership of planning and executing commissioning activities for complex electrical systems within a high-tech semiconductor facility. Your leadership will be key to aligning commissioning phases with ASHRAE standards, local regulations, and client specifications. This position requires both technical expertise and coordination across disciplines to ensure system performance and compliance throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement detailed electrical commissioning plans aligned with ASHRAE, LEED, Title 24, and client-specific standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review construction documents, sequence of operations, specifications, and IFC drawings to confirm design intent and testing coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finalize Factory Witness Testing (FWT) plans and conduct pre-shipment testing at vendor sites, ensuring equipment readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee installation verification, perform field inspections for electrical systems, and confirm code compliance and design accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead electrical Operational Acceptance Testing (OAT), Functional Acceptance Testing (FAT), and issue Green Tag certifications upon completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in Integrated Systems Testing (IST) to validate proper system interaction and support load testing, power quality analysis, and sequence validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and manage commissioning records using Smart Completions or equivalent tools, tracking deficiencies and corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce clear, comprehensive commissioning documentation, including test reports, non-conformance logs (NCLs), and owner turnover packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate closely with MEP inspectors, construction teams, vendors, and facilities personnel to ensure seamless project delivery and system readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead training sessions for facility operations teams and support post-occupancy commissioning, including LEED documentation and system optimization reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Any other duties or responsibilities that may be assigned to your in your role.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Skills Required:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years of electrical commissioning experience, preferably in semiconductor or high-tech environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth knowledge of NFPA 70E, OSHA, Title 24, LEED, and ASHRAE standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in electrical testing, SEL relay coordination, EMI shielding, and SEMI F47 compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication, planning, and technical documentation skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Education / Licenses / Certifications&lt;/h3&gt;
